   <concept id="DFARS-233.215"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">233.215</ph> Contract clause.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Use Alternate I of the clause at <ph xtrc="FARxref" class="- topic/ph ">FAR 52.233-1</ph>, Disputes, when—</p>
         <p outputclass="List2" class="- topic/p ">(1)  The acquisition is for—</p>
         <p outputclass="List3" class="- topic/p ">(i)  Aircraft</p>
         <p outputclass="List3" class="- topic/p ">(ii)  Spacecraft and launch vehicles</p>
         <p outputclass="List3" class="- topic/p ">(iii)  Naval vessels</p>
         <p outputclass="List3" class="- topic/p ">(iv)  Missile systems</p>
         <p outputclass="List3" class="- topic/p ">(v)  Tracked combat vehicles</p>
         <p outputclass="List3" class="- topic/p ">(vi)  Related electronic systems;</p>
         <p outputclass="List2" class="- topic/p ">(2)  The contracting officer determines that continued performance is—</p>
         <p outputclass="List3" class="- topic/p ">(i)  Vital to the national security, or</p>
         <p outputclass="List3" class="- topic/p ">(ii)  Vital to the public health and welfare; or</p>
         <p outputclass="List2" class="- topic/p ">(3)  The head of the contracting activity determines that continued performance is necessary pending resolution of any claim that might arise under or be related to the contract.</p>
      </conbody>
